cisc187.dna

Class FragmentList

  • java.lang.Object
    • cisc187.dna.FragmentList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Editable, Printable

    public class FragmentList
extends Object
implements Printable, Editable
    Contains an array of DNA/RNA BaseSequence character fragments. A DNA "fragment" is a sequence of either DNA characters, RNA characters, or an empty sequence. Sequencer commands that manipulate DNA sequences refer to methods manipulating sequences in this fragment list.

    Fragment capacity is fixed at construction time. Fragment entries with no BaseSequence characters within them will contain an EMPTY indicator. TODO: commands defined in the program could be an enum rather than naked strings.

    Since:
    03-25-2016
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:

        public void insert(int pos,
                   SequenceType type,
                   String sequence)
        Inserts a sequence to a specified position in the Fragment list. The SequenceType must be DNA or RNA and ensures it only contains appropriate letters for its type. Otherwise it will display an error. If there is currently a sequence in the specified position it is overwritten by the new sequence.
